post_text:
19 years ago we remember all of the rescue workers firefighters, police officers, and countless civilians who worked together in unity to find the fallen in the Twin Tower and Pentagon Attacks. We also serve to remember the passengers onboard each plane. We honor you and your service.

‚ÄúNow, we have inscribed a new memory alongside those others. It‚Äôs a memory of tragedy and shock, of loss and mourning. But not only of loss and mourning. It‚Äôs also a memory of bravery and self-sacrifice, and the love that lays down its life for a friend‚Äïeven a friend whose name it never knew.‚Äù ‚Äî George W. Bush

"So noone told you school was gonna be this way.
Clever has your class, it broke, you're trying to log on anyways.

We'll be there for you (throughout all of middle school)
We'll be there for you (because we love your kids too)

post_text: Today at 3pm the Governor will address his plan for reopening schools this fall. We are eager to reopen this fall and have been working studiously to make all the appropriate protocols and preparations regarding how this fall will look. After his announcement we anticipate that families will have tons of questions and many mixed emotions. Above all we are a team and family here at ICA and we will begin this process together. Please give us grace and have patience as we embark on this new year together. We will being by re-examining our protocols and working through new procedures. We want what is best for your children. We are here in support of you and the choices you make for your family. We are going to do everything we can to help all of our families navigate the uncharted territory of this fall. We will strive to make this year the best year for each child. #HerestoYear5 #PantherNation #WeAreInThisTogether #ICAFamily

ICA focuses this week as Staff Appreciation Week. All school staff is crucial to every students education. The moment a student walks into our school building they are greeted by our Fantastic Front Office Staff: Thank you Mrs. Dancy, Ms. Gomez, Mrs. Bernet, and Mrs. Pacitti.
Students are able to see how clean our school is thanks to our Amazing Facilities Crew Mr. Garnett, Ms. Jess, and Ms. Angie. Students are insured to get a warm meal, a cold milk, and maybe a sweet treat due to our Wonderful Cafeteria Staff Ms. Annette and Ms. Teresa.
Students are able to start or continue their day by having a study hall, and learn about different crafts in our before/after care ran by Ms. Selena and Ms. Terry.
All of these people make our school a marvelous place to learn each and everyday! Thank you ICA Staff!! #ICAStaffRock #WeAppreciateYou

post_text:
We are super proud of our top 24 ICA Spellers!

WAY TO GO!! #schoolchoiceweek

Today, at our 4th annual Scripps National Spelling Bee, 24 ICA students from grades one through eight competed to be our top speller. It came down to two after 11 rounds of nail biting spelling.

A 4th grader took 3rd place & the alternate spot for Regionals, while a 5th grade put up a valiant fight and earned second place. One of our seventh graders took first place with her vast knowledge of words. Every participant did an incredible job spelling today!

Now the top two are onto the Western Region District Spelling Bee at Salisbury Academy on Monday, February 24, at 6:30pm. We wish them the best of luck!

post_text:
We love hearing from our parents! ICA is celebrating National School Choice Week!

Oh the places your kids will go at ICA

This is our 2nd year at ICA and I couldn‚Äôt be happier. The make you feel welcome all the time. The staff ~ ALL staff ~ are involved in the daily happenings of the children. There are so many wonderful activities to allow children to express interest and learn new things.
Knowing that when a question or concern comes up, there are many individuals who can answer and address them.
I can see a HUGE difference in just 1 year within the school and academics. Growth is amazing to watch and witness.

If you‚Äôre struggling with your local school, I do recommend you come and visit and observe and speak to multiple families from ICA.

#schoolchoiceweek
